{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:45.620255+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cJY8M4 | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 761394d4c1bc093dffd57dd9d470512c6d645aaf)", "id": "lc_bd868aa6-3893-4e3c-a90b-e38212c403ca"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Default profile set shipped with vidpack.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Edit to customize or add profiles. Profile names must be lowercase ASCII.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | [web]\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | container = \"mp4\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | video_codec = \"libx264\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | audio_codec = \"aac\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | video_bitrate = \"2M\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | scale = \"1280:720\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | [archive]\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | container = \"mkv\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | video_codec = \"libx265\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | audio_codec = \"flac\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | crf = 18\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | scale = \"source\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | [gif]\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | container = \"gif\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | fps = 12\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | scale = \"480:-1\"\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Note: the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation,\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # the issue tracker.", "id": "lc_9275998a-428e-42a5-9ad3-1ac073f562cc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ebe8e51c-d167-46b9-9d25-008cf8fb9450", "tool_call_id": "call_cdbf6a515bb54206a05a5cdb", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:50.722876+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 120, "prompt_tokens": 3255, "total_tokens": 3375, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 56, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 2624}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "b338c76bda674a1e917e49640bba4aa8", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead7f-5c55-75b2-b9d8-edfe0b794dec-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C01_A03", "path": "README.md", "ref": "main"}, "id": "call_c333f184209f474eba0bbbaf", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3255, "output_tokens": 120, "total_tokens": 3375, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 2624}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 56}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:47:51.484674+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cJY8M4 | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: dd8f230ebcee1ed2c87953be052ec8d2681c21fc)", "id": "lc_454674d2-6c57-4a56-a3da-740fc48ad990"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:cJY8M4 | # vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | `vidpack` is a small Python CLI that runs FFmpeg using named profiles defined\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | in `profiles.toml`. The goal is to avoid memorizing long ffmpeg flag strings\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | for routine encoding jobs.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | FFmpeg is **not** bundled. `vidpack` expects `ffmpeg` (and `ffprobe`, where\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | relevant) to be available on `PATH`.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ## Install\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | pip install -e .\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | This registers the `vidpack` command.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ## Profiles\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | The default `profiles.toml` ships three profiles:\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | | Profile   | Container | Video codec | Audio codec | Notes                       |\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | |-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | | `web`     | mp4       | libx264     | aac         | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | | `archive` | mkv       | libx265     | flac        | source resolution, CRF 18   |\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | | `gif`     | gif       | (palette)   | (none)      | 480p wide, 12 fps           |\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | Edit `profiles.toml` to customize or add profiles.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ## Usage\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | vidpack <profile> <input> [-o OUTPUT] [--dry-run]\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | If `-o` is omitted, the output filename is derived from the input by\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | replacing the extension with the profile's container extension.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | `--dry-run` prints the ffmpeg command vidpack would run, without executing it.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | By default, vidpack will **not** overwrite an existing output file; it exits\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | with an error. Delete the output manually or pass a different `-o`.\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ## Examples\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Re-encode an mp4 for web at 720p\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | vidpack web input.mov -o talk.mp4\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Lossless-ish archive copy\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | vidpack archive input.mov\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | # Preview the ffmpeg command for the gif profile without running it\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | vidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ```\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | ## License\n| MCP:cJY8M4 | \n| MCP:cJY8M4 | MIT", "id": "lc_a7449ec3-27bd-46a5-ae69-8181ea5e155b"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ef2f630b-e283-4098-bfae-18ca471a996f", "tool_call_id": "call_c333f184209f474eba0bbbaf", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
